tissueExpression.summary: Moderate cytoplasmic positivity was displayed in respiratory epithelia, fallopian tube and skeletal myocytes. A subset of Leydig cells and stomach were strongly stained. Strong cytoplasmic and membranous staining was observed in a subset of salivary glandular cells while Purkinje cells exhibited strong cytoplasmic and nuclear positivity. Neuronal cells showed moderate cytoplasmic and nuclear staining. Remaining normal tissues were weakly stained or negative.
tissueExpression.validation: Mainly consistent with RNA expression data
Partly consistent with extensive gene/protein characterization data

image.description: Immunohistochemical staining of human cerebellum shows strong cytoplasmic and nuclear positivity in Purkinje cells.

tissueExpression.summary: A few cases of liver cancers and several endometrial cancers displayed moderate cytoplasmic and membranous immunoreactivity. Remaining cancer tissues were generally negative.
